metadata.name: a fortiori #155
metadata.description:
Energy is everywhere: it‚Äôs moving our bodies, buzzing around a city, growing the universe, and connecting everything within it. Perhaps the strongest symbol humans use for energy ‚Äì for ideas, life, and the various incarnations of power ‚Äì is light itself. 

For centuries, each form of art has tried to capture the energetic luminescence of a bright light, a warm glow, a spark... if we could only draw with its pure brilliance! From Caravaggio‚Äôs diagonal beams, to Picasso drawing with light across Gjon Mili‚Äôs photographic emulsions‚Ä¶ this pursuit persists through obsessive efforts by artists of every media. 

a fortiori seeks to capture this power of light with code, output on the native illumination of modern screens. The visual deconstruction of light and its reassembly into a frozen moment produces the tangible shards of each spark ‚Äì resulting in a sum of marks that exceeds the value of their individual parts. It‚Äôs then the obsessive energy of generative art‚Äôs looping and controlled randomness that enable its repeated mark making, of all types, to express the nearly-intangible intensity of light.

What one hand might communicate in drawing, with light or stick or keyboard, 100 hands would therefore say 100 times louder, clearer, and more impactfully. And if one could capture the authentic energy of traveling light in a single image, it stands to reason that 500 of these images will multiply their energy-inducing qualities together, and exponentially grow their collective power. In this idea, the medium is the message ‚Äì proving the power of the medium, and its ability to generate energy.


--------

TENDER x Thomas Noya
December 2022

Source code is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License as published by the Free Software Foundation.

a fortiori was created in p5.js and is optimized for live output in Chrome. Press these keys in live view to control the art and render high resolution versions of any token:

x = pause
y = play
1 = 1000x1000
2-9 = 2000x2000, ‚Ä¶, 9000x9000
0 = 10000x10000
t = 12500x12500
f = 15000x15000
s = save PNG

Outputs beyond 10,000 pixels square are dependent on individual computer and browser capabilities. 

10% of all primary and secondary proceeds donated directly to Girls Who Code

metadata.name: 3ASF #37
metadata.description:
3 Armonografos Sobre Figuras / 3 Harmonographs on Shapes

"If I had to choose, the harmonograph is my preferred mechanism for making gen art"

The composition works with three harmonographs vertically distributed with 2 pendulums each that draw on black and white shapes. It is a game between the positive and the negative.

Steps-Layers:

1 - White or black background
2 - Draw shape 1 (triangle or Circle or Rectangle) with the opposite tone to the background.
3 - Draw shape 2 (triangle or Circle or Rectangle) same tone as the background.
4 - Draw the 3 Harmonographs. The (inverted) tones depend on the tones of the shapes and background.
5 - Cutting / glitch effect. Vertical and horizontal.
6 - Symmetries X or Y or XY or none are applied.
7 - Rectangles are cut again (yes/no)

// ---

"Si tuviese que elegir, el armonografo es mi mecanismo preferido para hacer arte generativo"

La composici√≥n trabaja con tres arm√≥nografos de 2 p√©ndulos distribu√≠dos verticalmente que dibujan sobre figuras en blanco y negro. Es un juego entre positivos y negativos.

Pasos-Capas: 

1 - Fondo blanco o negro
2 - Dibuja figura 1 (triangulo o Circulo o Rectangulo) con tono opuesto al fondo.
3 - Dibuja figura 2 (triangulo o Circulo o Rectangulo) mismo tono que el fondo.
4 - Dibuja los 3 Armon√≥grafos. Los tonos (invertidos) dependen de los tonos de la figura y el fondo.
5 - Se corta / efecto glitch. Vertical y horizontal.
6 - Se aplican simetrias X o Y o XY o ninguna.
7 - Se cortan nuevamente rect√°ngulos (si/no)

// ---
Keys:

[1,2,3] -> change pixel density. Or can be passed via url ?pd=5 6000x9000pix. Be aware for the file size in render. 
[s] -> download canvas capture. Different pixel density, different sizes.
[double tap] -> download canvas capture on mobile

metadata.name: (DE)STRUCTURAL #35
metadata.description:
"Reserve a spot for your family and loved ones in our brand new *floating* high rise condominiums. Leave the dirty air of Level-1 behind! Discount of 200'000'000 credits applicable is you already own any of our apartments in another sector."

Like with my previous works, each variation starts as an empty black canvas in the depth of your [CALCULATING MACHINE]. With your [UNIQUE PURCHASE TRANSACTION RECEIPT] specially constructed AI engineers start to envision a condominium that is perfect just for you! Utilizing both the [CENTRAL PROCESSING UNIT] and [GRAPHICS PROCESSING UNIT] the blueprints materialize in front of your [ORGANS OF VISION OR OF LIGHT SENSITIVITY]. Everything is procedurally generated taking in hundreds of randomized parameters bound to specific rules of construction.

Orbit: mouse [PRIMARY] button.
Pan: mouse [SECONDARY] button.
Zoom: mouse [GYRATION DISC].
Cycle light intensity levels: [B]

metadata.name: Endeavor #38
metadata.description:
Endeavor is a generative system structured to create abstract mountains.

When I look at the outputs, I am reminded of the things I would like to achieve. I would be curious to know what comes to your mind when you ask yourself, "What is my goal? What do I intend to do?"

Controls:

'p' - Play an animation that draws the mountain layer by layer
'1' - Default, textured image
'2' - No border
'3' - Flat, non-textured image
'4' - Flat with no border

Each of the 128 editions chooses one of five forms, all of which explore variety in layout, shading, and color composition.

25% of the royalties for each edition will pass to the original minter.

Each output is generated from code written in p5js.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Swedish Forest #53
metadata.description:
If I had to choose a place where time was frozen and where I could contemplate the landscape for eternity this place would be a scandinavian forest.
I have been contemplating these kind of landscape for a very long time both in Sweden and in the Pyrenees where the ecosystem is very similar.
This project generates an illustration of a scandinavian forest in many different situations. At day and at night, in every season of the year, next to a lake or not, with steep hills or at the plains, snowing, with preponderance of some plant species over others, etc.
The artwork is also drawn in various paint modes and layouts.

The sun or the moon may be visible, the moon shows always the actual moon phase based on the current date.
The reflection on the lake is the fxhash morse endcoded.


Developed in vanilla js using svg and canvas
Rendering can be unresponsive on slow devices
Click or touch to switch to Parallax mode, just move the mouse or finger.


[S] Download in SVG format
[D] Download in PNG format

Features:

Layout: Landscape, Portrait, Square
PredominantSpecies: Blueberry, Lingonberry, Calluna, Rocks, None
Trees: Mixed, PinesAndFirs, Birches, None
Season: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter
DayNight: Day, Night
PaintStyle: Normal, Stroke, Paint, WhiteOnBlack, BlackOnWhite
ColorStyle: Normal, Crazy
HasLake: True, False
HasTrees: None, Few, Many, Crowded

Created by Daniel Juli√† Lundgren, fxhash: danieljulia.tez, twitter: @daniel_julia. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Artifice #216
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‚ÄòS‚Äô : save as png (3000‚Ää√ó‚Ää3600)
‚ÄôV‚Äô : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‚Äòg=n‚Äô : no grain
‚Äòg=p‚Äô : paper grain
‚Äòh=t‚Äô : high resolution mode, 9000‚Ää√ó10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append ‚Äú&g=p&h=t‚Äù to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.
